Description: Odonate Therapeutics is dedicated to the development of therapeutics that improve and extend the lives of patients with cancer.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Odonate Therapeutics is a pharmaceutical company dedicated to the development of best-in-class therapeutics that improve and extend the lives of patients with cancer. Our initial focus is on the development of tesetaxel, a novel chemotherapy agent that belongs to a class of drugs known as taxanes, which are widely used in the treatment of cancer. Tesetaxel has several potential therapeutic advantages over currently available taxanes, including: oral administration with a low pill burden and a patient-friendly dosing regimen; a formulation that does not contain solubilizing agents that are known to cause hypersensitivity (allergic) reactions; and improved activity against chemotherapy-resistant tumors. Tesetaxel has been generally well tolerated in clinical studies and has demonstrated robust single-agent antitumor activity in two Phase 2 studies in patients with locally advanced or metastatic breast cancer ("MBC").

Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: City Walker is a local guide in your pocket - day or night. No longer have a generic experience in a city, let City Walker guide you to the best local spots within minutes of your current location. It provides a fast and reliable way to discover local hidden gems. Start exploring and have immersive experiences when it comes to food, drinks, coffee and even a little culture all with your own two feet. It’s simple - here’s how it works: - Download and open the app, sign in, tap a custom city category, pre-populated category or let City Walker Walk You To It using our suggestion engine The app will use your location to begin ranking businesses around you You’ll be presented with results all within a 15 minute walking distance of you - fueled by the input of local residents - Tap on a place, see images, hours and descriptions If the place looks interesting tap on the map to get turn by turn directions Don’t forget to leave your POV! Even if you aren’t a local, City Walker wants to hear what you think Don’t want to debate options? Simply tap Walk me to it and using your location, City Walker delivers the best single experience for you. Its spontaneous and easy but relax knowing that all results are based on our hyper local data. Locals can rediscover their neighborhood, curate and build up the community as well as promote local business. Earn badges for your POVs and check ins plus share local spots right to your social feed. Only in town for a short while? City Walker App is a great way to prioritize your time in a new place. Experience not only the best, but the most a town has to offer using City Walker App. If you’re visiting a new city, a resident or just returning home for the weekend in search of something new, City Walker App is the perfect travel app. Explore the culture the way only locals can — find the hidden gem instantly... with City Walker. After you visit a place, we ask you share your Point of View on City Walker - good or bad. You’re point of view is not only improves the profile for the business and passes down local knowledge, it directly affects the search rank of that business. Unlike other travel app a business can’t pay to promote themselves in our ranked metric results. We don’t care how much money a business has, we care that people have a great experience. The community is the business's marketing team and it’s this approach that levels the playing field for local business. On City Walker it doesn’t matter how much money you have for advertising, what matters is that your customers are passionate and share experiences about you. Our goal is simple: live local. Like us on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/citywalkerapp Follow us on Instagram at https://www.instagram.com/citywalkerapp/ Follow us on Twitter at https://twitter.com/citywalkerapp

Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: American wind turbine manufacturers, designers, & engineers supplying small and medium vertical axis wind turbines to the USA, UK, Europe, & South America. Started in 2009 by a team of wind power technology engineers in Solon, Ohio: Jeff Milbourn (CEO), Gerry Sposato (VP & Marketing COO), & John Rexford (Senior VP of Engineering).  Current wind turbine models include the AW 50, AW 20, and AW-L (low wind) units. Argosy Wind Power customizes units to fit specific certification requirements by the EIC in addition to country & tax rebate or incentive specific specs. The AW 20 meets the IEC standard for Class I wind turbines, and the AW 50 and AW 50-L models are Class II IEC compliant. Argosy Wind Power continues to work with community wind projects and renewable energy investors around the world. The focus of their community wind turbine & wind farm projects is to make adjustments to their products to make them compliant with local wind energy production rebates, financial incentives, and government and/or municipal electrical grid connections.   Feed-in-tariff (FIT) compliant wind power schemes in Europe, particularly the UK and Italy, are among the largest markets served by Argosy Wind Power. Argosy Wind Power's executive team are also engineers who still help develop new wind power technologies. Argosy Wind Power's proprietary permanent magnet, direct drive wind turbine technology aims to minimize the need for maintenance & maximize energy production.  Argosy Wind Power is a member of the American Wind Energy Association (AWEA), Renewable UK (RUK), & Distributed Wind Energy Association (DWEA).
